ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Renting and leasing of other machinery, equipment and tangible goods
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Leasing or rental services concerning other machinery and equipment without operator n.e.c.
CPA 2.1_Name: Rental and leasing services of other machinery and equipment without operator and tangible goods n.e.c.
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- rental, leasing or hiring services concerning all kinds of machinery, whether or not electrical, except personal or household goods, generally used as capital goods by industry, without operator, such as:
  • engines and turbines
  • machine tools
  • mining and oil field equipment
  • coin-operated gambling machines
  • exhibition material
  • motion picture production equipment
  • professional, scientific measuring and control apparatus
  • other commercial and industrial machinery
CPA 2.1_Exclude:
This subcategory excludes:
- rental, leasing or hiring services concerning agricultural and forestry machinery and equipment without operator, see 77.31.10
- rental, leasing or hiring services concerning construction and civil engineering machinery and equipment without operator, see 77.32.10
- rental, leasing or hiring services concerning office machinery, furniture and equipment without operator, see 77.33.11
- rental, leasing or hiring services concerning computers, without operator, see 77.33.12

ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Employment activities
Activities of employment placement agencies
Activities of employment placement agencies
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Executive/retained search services
CPA 2.1_Name: Executive search services
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- specialised search and recruitment services limited to filling highly paid executive, senior manager, and professional positions, according to client specifications. Included are the services of:
  • conducting detailed interviews with the client organisation's management team 
  • developing job profiles, conducting original research and advertising to locate potential job candidates 
  • screening possible candidates, preparing, presenting, and discussing a confidential list of highly qualified applicants with the client 
  • making interview arrangements, negotiating compensation, and providing post-hire follow-up
The prospective employee/client makes the decision as to which candidate to hire. The fee for the services provided is charged whether or not the candidate is hired. This service is also known as retained search.
CPA 2.1_CPA 2.1 label: Executive search services
CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Executive/retained search services

ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Activities of employment placement agencies
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Contract staffing services
CPA 2.1_Name: Executive search services
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- specialised search and recruitment services limited to filling highly paid executive, senior manager, and professional positions, according to client specifications. Included are the services of:
  • conducting detailed interviews with the client organisation's management team 
  • developing job profiles, conducting original research and advertising to locate potential job candidates 
  • screening possible candidates, preparing, presenting, and discussing a confidential list of highly qualified applicants with the client 
  • making interview arrangements, negotiating compensation, and providing post-hire follow-up
The prospective employee/client makes the decision as to which candidate to hire. The fee for the services provided is charged whether or not the candidate is hired. This service is also known as retained search.
CPA 2.1_CPA 2.1 label: Executive search services
CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Contract staffing services

ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Activities of employment placement agencies
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Contract staffing services
CPA 2.1_Name: Permanent placement services, other than executive search services
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- testing, interviewing, reference checking, evaluation and counselling of prospective employees
- recruiting, selecting and referring candidates to the client to fill positions on a permanent (indeterminate) basis

The services may be procured by the potential employer or by the prospective employee. The candidate is selected and hired by the prospective employee. The placement firm is paid on a contingency basis, i.e. only for successful placement of a candidate. This subcategory includes permanent placement services for a complete range of occupations from low-level employees to management employees, including executives, except those recruited through executive/retained search, and for domestic or international job placements.
CPA 2.1_Exclude:
This subcategory excludes:
- services of personal theatrical or artistic agents or agencies, see 74.90.20
CPA 2.1_CPA 2.1 label: Permanent placement services, other than executive search services
CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Contract staffing services

CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Reservation services for air transportation
CPA 2.1_Name: Reservation services for airlines
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- arranging reservations for airline tickets

These services include obtaining a client's requirements, advising on alternatives, assisting in the client's choice and may include issuance of airline tickets on behalf of the service provider. They are often provided in person, by telephone or over the Internet. Respective reselling services are also included. The reservations can be for domestic and international transport.

ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Organization of conventions and trade shows
Organization of conventions and trade shows
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Convention assistance and organization services
CPA 2.1_Name: Convention organisation services
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- organisation and management of conventions and congresses and provision of convention assistance and support services, with or without own staff, including components such as:
  • advice and consultancy services with respect to all aspects of the organisation of conventions, including defining objectives, financing, e.g. through sponsorship, exhibitions, loans and registration fees, estimating income and expenditure budgets and other financial matters 
  • assistance in choosing and locating space, venue research, feasibility and negotiation
  • marketing and public relations for the convention or congress, speaker liaison
  • organisation or provision of secretariat and office facilities and staff for conference registration, conference administration, conference documentation and abstract handling, translation of documents etc.
  • organisation or supply of simultaneous interpretation and other on-site services
  • supply of registration processing systems, electronic information and design
  • supply and setting up of equipment such as audiovisual equipment associated with the organisation of the event
  • organisation or provision of accommodation booking service including negotiating group discounts, delegate transfers and on-site transportation services, food and beverage arrangements, and tour programmes

Payment for these services can be through fees assessed to organisers and exhibitors, as well as entry fees for visitors.
CPA 2.1_CPA 2.1 label: Convention organisation services
CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Convention assistance and organization services

  • assistance in choosing and locating space, venue research, feasibility and negotiation
  • marketing and public relations for the trade show or trade fair
  • organisation or provision of secretariat and office facilities and staff for trade show or trade fair registration, administration, documentation, translation of documents etc.
  • organisation or supply of other on-site services
  • supply of registration processing systems, electronic information and design
  • supply and setting up of equipment such as audiovisual equipment associated with the organisation of the event
  • organisation or provision of accommodation booking service including negotiating group discounts, on-site transportation services, food and beverage arrangements

CPA 2.1_Name: Pre-primary education services
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- education services usually provided by nursery schools, kindergartens, pre-schools, centres for early childhood education, centres for infant education or special sections attached to primary schools. 

Pre-primary education (ISCED Level 0) is defined as the initial stage of organised instruction designed primarily to introduce very young children to a school-type environment, that is, to provide a bridge between the home and a school-based atmosphere.
CPA 2.1_Exclude:
This subcategory excludes:
- day camps for children, see 55.30.12
- child day-care services, see 88.91.1
CPA 2.1_CPA 2.1 label: Pre-primary education services
CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Pre-primary education services

ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Higher education
Higher education
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Post-secondary non-tertiary education services, general
CPA 2.1_Name: On-line post-secondary non-tertiary general education services
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- on-line educational services for programmes (ISCED Level 4) which, while happening after students finish upper secondary education, they cannot be considered tertiary education because content-wise these programmes are not significantly more advanced than those from upper secondary. They are either short vocational programmes that lead students to the labour market or programmes with substantial theoretical background instruction specifically designed to prepare students for entry to tertiary education in cases where they had previously followed a curriculum (in Level 3 above) that lacked elements needed to entitle them to enter tertiary education programmes. 

Services in this subcategory cover education which is not designed explicitly to prepare participants for a specific class of occupations or trades or for entry into further vocational or technical education programmes.
CPA 2.1_CPA 2.1 label: On-line post-secondary non-tertiary general education services
CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Post-secondary non-tertiary education services, general

CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- on-line educational services for programmes (ISCED Level 4) which, while happening after students finish upper secondary education, they cannot be considered tertiary education because content-wise these programmes are not significantly more advanced than those from upper secondary. They are either short vocational programmes that lead students to the labour market or programmes with substantial theoretical background instruction specifically designed to prepare students for entry to tertiary education in cases where they had previously followed a curriculum (in Level 3 above) that lacked elements needed to entitle them to enter tertiary education programmes. 

Services in this subcategory cover education that prepares participants for direct entry, without further training, into specific occupations. Successful completion of such programmes leads to a labour-market relevant vocational qualification.

Sports and recreation education
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Sports and recreation education services
CPA 2.1_Name: Sports and recreation education services
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes sports instruction services by sports camps and schools or by professional sports instructors, teachers or coaches to groups of individuals. It does not include the provision of such services by academic schools, colleges and universities.
This subcategory includes:
- sports instruction (baseball, basketball, cricket, football, hockey, tennis, figure skating, etc.)
- camps, sports instruction
- gymnastics instruction
- riding instruction
- swimming instruction
- martial arts instruction
- card game instruction (such as bridge)
- yoga instruction
CPA 2.1_Exclude:
This subcategory excludes:
- recreational or vacation camps that include sports training or instruction, see 55.30.12
- incidental sports and recreation instruction by academic schools, colleges or universities, see 85.10-85.42
- cultural education services, see 85.52
CPA 2.1_CPA 2.1 label: Sports and recreation education services
CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Sports and recreation education services

CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Other miscellaneous services n.e.c.
CPA 2.1_Name: Coin-operated machine services n.e.c.
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- services rendered by coin-operated machines, such as blood pressure measuring, scales, lockers, shoe shining machines, photographic booths etc.

“Coin-operated machines” are in this context self-service machines (i.e. without human intervention), regardless of mode of payment, such as coins, credit cards etc.
CPA 2.1_Exclude:
This subcategory excludes:
- coin-operated games and gambling machine services, see 92.00.12, 93.29.22
- coin-operated laundry services, see 96.01.11

ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Activities of households as employers of domestic personnel
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Domestic services
CPA 2.1_Name: Services of households as employers of domestic personnel providing assistance services for the elderly, without medical care
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- services provided by private households as employers of personnel providing everyday assistance services for living at home for non-autonomous elderly people, such as:
  • washing and dressing, eating, administrative obligations, intellectual and social life
  • shopping and preparation of meals
  • nursing at home without medical care and assistance to mobility
  • other assistance services for living at home for non-autonomous elderly people (housework, washing and ironing etc.)

ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Activities of households as employers of domestic personnel
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Domestic services
CPA 2.1_Name: Services of households as employers of domestic personnel providing assistance services for disabled adults, without medical care
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- services provided by private households as employers of personnel providing everyday assistance services for living at home for disabled adults, such as:
  • washing and dressing, eating, administrative obligations, intellectual and social life
  • shopping and preparation of meals
  • nursing at home without medical care and assistance to mobility
  • other assistance services for living at home for non-autonomous disabled adults (housework, washing and ironing etc.)

CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Domestic services

ISIC Rev. 4_Description: Activities of households as employers of domestic personnel
CPC 2.1_CPC21title: Domestic services
CPA 2.1_Name: Services of households as employers of domestic personnel providing housing and household assistance services for daily life
CPA 2.1_Include:
This subcategory includes:
- services provided by private households as employers of personnel providing a wide range of everyday assistance services, such as:
  • housework and “handyman” services at home, gardening, home guard services, washing, cleaning and ironing services for households at home, shopping and preparation of meals, walking, feeding and care for pets at home.
- services provided by private households as employers of specialised personnel providing specialised not-everyday assistance services, such as:
  • IT technical support services, home school support courses, hairdressing and other beauty treatment services at home.
CPA 2.1_CPA 2.1 label: Services of households as employers of domestic personnel providing housing and household assistance services for daily life
CPA 2.1_CPC 2.1 label: Domestic services
